The paper focuses on the problem of duplicate crowdtesting reports detection, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The proposed method involves using both textual descriptions and screenshots, which suggests the use of information retrieval (cs.IR) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques. Additionally, the use of textual features such as TF-IDF and word embeddings suggests the use of natural language processing (cs.CL).
